HEADWORD: Revindicate
<hw>Re*vin"di*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>re-</ets> + <ets>vindicate</ets>. Cf. <er>Revindicate</er>,
<er>Revenge</er>.]</ety> <def>To vindicate again; to reclaim; to demand
and take back.</def> <rj><au>Mitford.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

